<div class="homepage-top-message">
<h3 style="color: #d90000; font-weight: bold;"><a href="/resources/parent/corona-virus" style="color: #d90000; font-weight: bold;"><div class="article-image-placeholder-left"><img src="/images/homepage/banners/coronavirus.jpg" width="200" alt="Image of the Cronavirus" title="Image of the Cronavirus"></div>
							Coronavirus Update (04/22/2020)
						</a></h3>
<div>
<br>
						For the latest information regarding the Coronavirus, please visit our
						<a href="/resources/parent/corona-virus">
							Coronavirus Resources page.
						</a><br>
						For Remote Access Learning help please visit our:
						<br><br><a href="https://tutorials.levittownschools.com/Remote%20Access%20Learning%20Resources%20For%20Parents/" target="https://tutorials.levittownschools.com/Remote%20Access%20Learning%20Resources%20For%20Parents/">
							Remote Access Learning Tutorials for Parents/Students
						</a><br><br><a href="https://tutorials.levittownschools.com/Remote%20Access%20Learning/" target="https://tutorials.levittownschools.com/Remote%20Access%20Learning/">
							Remote Access Learning Tutorials Teachers
						</a><br clear="all"><hr>
</div>
</div>
<br clear="all"><div class="homepage-top-message">
<h3>
						Parent Portal Update
					</h3>
<span class="homepage-top-message-delimiter">-</span><div>
					 Report Cards for the 2nd Quarter are now available on the <a href="https://ps.levittownschools.com/public/" target="https://ps.levittownschools.com/public/">Parent Portal</a> for High School and Middle School students.
						
					</div>
</div>
<br clear="all"><div class="homepage-top-message">
<h3>
						School Board and Budget Election Update
					</h3>
<span class="homepage-top-message-delimiter">-</span><div>
						All deadlines associated with the Budget Vote (including the submission of the Nominating Petitions, Campaign Expenditure Statements, Lottery, etc.) are all on hold as they are all based on the date of the Budget and School Board Election which to date is unknown.   In addition, Executive Order 202.13 required that beginning March 31, 2020, the circulation, filing and collection of any petitions that would otherwise be circulated under the Education Law is required to be postponed. Therefore, all associated deadlines are on hold and pending further executive order.
						<br><br><a href="/boe/Candidate's%20Package%20-%20English.pdf?v=2020042636#page=1&amp;navpanes=0%0D%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20" target="_pdf">
							Candidate's Packet for Election to the Board of Education
						</a><br><a href="/boe/Candidate's%20Package%20-%20Spanish.pdf?v=2020042636#page=1&amp;navpanes=0%0D%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20" target="_pdf">
							Candidate's Packet for Election to the Board of Education (Spanish)
						</a><br>
</div>
</div>
<br clear="all"><div class="homepage-top-message">
<h3>
						Private/Parochial Transportation Application Deadline Extended to May 9, 2020
					</h3>
<span class="homepage-top-message-delimiter">-</span><div>
						Please note that due to the closure of schools pursuant to the Executive Order(s) issued by the Governor for the COVID-19 crisis and recognizing that such requests need to be incorporated into a school district's budget, the Department directs all public school districts to accept all parental requests for transportation to charter and nonpublic schools submitted on or before May 9, 2020. The Department deems such Executive Order(s) be a reasonable excuse for a delay under Ed. Law 3635.
						<a href="/district/forms/rft/">
							Click here for more information/application.
						</a>
</div>
</div>
<br clear="all"><div class="homepage-top-message">
<h3>
						Reminder
					</h3>
<span class="homepage-top-message-delimiter">-</span><div>
						We hope things are well with you and your family. Governor Cuomo's Executive Order has mandated that all people work from home, except for essential services.  To be in compliance with the Governor's order, moving forward, tech related questions should first be directed to the classroom teacher, who will then forward these concerns to the appropriate staff member. Please expect a delay as we will be functioning with a reduced work force.
					</div>
</div>
<br clear="all"><div class="homepage-top-message">
<h3>
						Capital Construction Project Summary
					</h3>
